name: mole_fraction_of_glyoxal_in_air
description: Mole fraction is used in the construction "mole_fraction_of_X_in_Y", where X is a material constituent of Y. A chemical species denoted by X may be described by a single term such as "nitrogen" or a phrase such as "nox_expressed_as_nitrogen". The chemical formula for glyoxal is CHOCHO. The IUPAC name for glyoxal is ethanedial.
